# Terraform Guidelines

## Project Structure
- Organize code in logical modules
- Use separate files for different resource types
- Implement proper variable and output organization
- Follow naming conventions for resources
- Use workspaces for different environments

## Variables
- Define variables with proper types
- Use sensible defaults for variables
- Implement proper variable validation
- Use tfvars files for environment-specific values
- Follow naming conventions for variables

## Modules
- Create reusable modules for common infrastructure
- Use proper module input and output definitions
- Version modules appropriately
- Document module usage and parameters
- Follow module best practices

## State Management
- Use remote state storage (S3, etc.)
- Implement proper state locking
- Handle state migration when needed
- Use state backends appropriately
- Secure access to state files

## Resources
- Follow proper resource naming conventions
- Use appropriate resource dependencies
- Implement proper resource lifecycle management
- Use count and for_each appropriately
- Handle resource drift properly

## Security
- Store sensitive data in secure backends
- Use appropriate IAM roles and policies
- Implement proper network security
- Follow security best practices
- Scan for security vulnerabilities

## Providers
- Use appropriate provider versions
- Configure providers properly
- Handle provider-specific configurations
- Use multiple providers when needed
- Follow provider best practices

## Outputs
- Define clear, meaningful outputs
- Use outputs for inter-module communication
- Implement proper output validation
- Follow naming conventions for outputs
- Document output purposes

## Testing
- Write comprehensive tests for modules
- Use Terratest for infrastructure testing
- Validate configurations before applying
- Test infrastructure changes appropriately
- Follow testing best practices

## Version Control
- Store Terraform code in version control
- Use appropriate .gitignore files
- Handle sensitive data appropriately
- Follow branching strategies for infrastructure
- Use pull requests for infrastructure changes

## Remote Backends
- Use remote backends for team collaboration
- Implement proper backend configuration
- Handle backend initialization properly
- Secure access to remote backends
- Use appropriate backend types

## Formatting and Style
- Use terraform fmt for consistent formatting
- Follow HCL syntax best practices
- Use proper indentation and spacing
- Implement consistent naming conventions
- Write clear, descriptive comments